subSubSection.paragraph:
Opercle with a single sharp spine at level of ventral margin of pupil (when viewed from side); margin of interopercle smooth except for three or four (two to five in 
paratypes
) tiny, close-set serrae on a small bony prominence at upper end; preopercle broadly rounded, its free edge smooth except for slight indentation at pore sites, extending downward and forward from level of ventral edge of orbit to slightly in front of a vertical at posterior edge of orbit.
